    • isAfter

      public boolean isAfter(int a, int b)
      Returns whether the coordinate a comes after b.

      For example, if navigating downwards, 2 comes after 1, while the opposite is true if navigating upwards. This always returns false if two arguments are equal.

      Returns:
      whether the coordinate a comes after b
